FBIS3-7230 "dreas059__a94012" FBIS-EAS-94-059-A Document Type:Daily Report 28 March 1994 ANNEX Japan Hosokawa Backs ROK Bid for UNSC Seat OW2503112594 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 25 Mar Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW2503112594 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN Language: Japanese Article Type:BFN [Text] During a meeting with ROK President Kim Yong-sam on 24 March, Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa expressed his backing to South Korea for its plan to apply for nonpermanent membership of the UN Security Council [UNSC] in 1995. Besides South Korea, Sri Lanka has also announced candidacy for the UNSC seat to be vacated by Pakistan, the present representative for Asia in the council.
